What is a Banya and how I get you high?

Banya is a process of deep cleansing of the soul and body in combination with massage, aromatherapy and meditation. This is the way to calm down, relax and purify.
I will reboot the nervous system with the help of temperature difference aromatherapy and rhythmic massage with veniks in the Banya!

How is the steaming procedure going?

Getting to know each other + warming up
The temperature in the Bath is just 122 F.
We are sitting comfortably and warming up. We breathe the fresh frosty air from the open windows. We drink tea, get acquainted, and discuss what will happen.
1
The first steam
Mint-anise steam with juniper. Sprinkling and light steaming
2
Concentrated steam
Accentuated soaring of the legs with oak brooms. The contrast of the icy sheet and the cooling of the head with mint water. Active hot steaming with oak brooms. The contrast in the icy cold pluche is 8°C.
3
Rest on the couch. Tea.
You will take a 15 minutes rest and even will try to have a nep
4
Broom steaming with juniper and reheating on a sharp steam with oak veniks
5
Scrubs (optional)
Rub with honey crumbs with ground pine nuts, mint, eucalyptus and chamomile or birch tar washing
6
The final steam on baked potatoes
Steam inhalation on baked potatoes with garlic and dill. Warming up with fans in wormwood steam.
7
Farewell to tears

Mission

My mission revolves around creating a sustainable business model that enables single mothers worldwide to earn a daily income as steam masters in Banyas.

Beginning in the USA and expanding to Ukraine and Russia, I aim to build a network of Banyas, accumulating profits and donations for further expansion.
Furthermore, I'm committed to addressing the psychological recovery needs of individuals affected by war.

By utilizing Banyas as a platform for mental healing, I envision creating a PTSD recovery therapy program based on the therapeutic aspects of the Banya experience

About me

About me

My name is Sanya.

I'm from Crimea, I've been living in Moscow for the last few years.

After the war began, my friend Chris helped me, as a Ukrainian, with moving to the United States, where a year and a half later I decided to build a business in a Russian Bathhouse - Banya..

It doesn't sound politically correct to most people on the planet, but I don't give a fuck. I make the product I believe in.
